TELEFLEX, INC., Plaintiff-Appellee, v. FICOSA NORTH AMERICA CORP., Fico Cables, S.A., and Ficosa North America S.A. De C.V., Defendants-Appellants. Teleflex, Inc., Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Ficosa North America Corp., Fico Cables, S.A., and Ficosa North America S.A. De C.V., Defendants-Appellees. Nos. 01-1372, 01-1397. United States Court of Appeals, Federal Circuit. Jan. 31, 2002.

ON MOTION

ORDER

Teleflex, Inc. moves to voluntarily dismiss its appeal 01-1397. Teleflex states that Ficosa North America Corp. et al. do not oppose, but reserve the right to move for sanctions.

Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED THAT:

(1) The unopposed motion to dismiss 01-1397 is granted.

(2) The revised official caption for 01-1372 is reflected above.
